description.p:
a first step of obtaining a glass fiber by heating, melting, and drawing a glass preform;


a second step of preparing a primary coating resin and a secondary coating resin such that an adhesion force S (g/cm) at the interface between the primary coating resin after curing and the glass fiber is at least 1/13 ((g/cm)/ (degree)  C.) with respect to a glass transition temperature Tg ( (degree)  C.) of the secondary coating resin after curing;


a third step of simultaneously applying the primary coating resin and secondary coating resin to an outer periphery of the glass fiber; and


a fourth step of photo-curing the primary coating resin and secondary coating resin to yield the coated optical fiber.

FIG. 1 is a graph schematically showing a relationship of relaxation modulus of a resin with respect to temperature thereof;


